                    <death when="0424" syriaca-computed-start="0424-01-01" source="#bib1349-2">424</death>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1349-2">BHO, 783.
Hoffmann, Ausziige, 28- 33.
Fiey, "Ma'In" , 437-53.</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1349">Maʿin was a general of Shapur II. He became
          a Christian when he witnesses the martyrdom of <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1194">Dōdō</persName>. He was baptized and arrested. He
          built 69 places of worship around <placeName ref=" http://syriaca.org/place/184">Sinjar</placeName>. He died at age 114 in a monastery that he built near <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/83">Europos</placeName>.</note>
                    <note type="disambiguation">with Dōdō</note>
                    <event type="attestation" xml:id="attestation1349-1" source="#bib1349-2">
                        <p xml:lang="en">Maʿin is commemorated in <title ref="http://syriaca.org/work/1226">Maʿin (text)</title>.</p>
                    </event>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1349-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="la">Bibliotheca Hagiographica Syriaca</title>
